{
  "translations": [
    {
      "unit_id": "p20_g02",
      "translation": "Although VONB of US$2.765 billion in 2020 decreased by 33% compared to 2019, we rapidly adopted new digital tools, and the widespread relaxation of movement restrictions supported the recovery of sales momentum. AIA China made the largest contribution to the Group's VONB in 2020 and was our first reporting segment to show recovery in sales momentum, as the region gradually eased strict lockdowns from March 2020 onwards. Excluding the low-level sales from mainland Chinese visitors to Hong Kong, VONB in the Group's other segments showed strong recovery in the second half, growing 23% compared to the first half. The Group's new business development momentum remained strong in 2021, with VONB in the first two months 15% higher than the same period in 2020."
    }
  ]
}
```
